Risk Management Program (RMP) Executive Summary
CF Industries Sales, LLC, Glenwood Terminal

Glenwood Terminal and the regulated substances handled:
Glenwood Terminal stores and distributes anhydrous ammonia. The regulated substances, as defined by 40 CFR Part 68, which are present at the facility in more than the threshold quantity are anhydrous ammonia.

The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps:
The Glenwood Terminal has taken all the necessary steps to comply with all of the accidental release and chemical-specific prevention requirements as set forth in U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) 40 CFR Part 68. This facility is also subject to the U.S. Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Process Safety Management (PSM) standard 29 CFR 1910.119. The following summarizes the elements of the release and chemical-specific prevention that are in place at our facility:
-	Process safety information that is accurate and up to date;
-	Well-trained operating, maintenance, and contract personnel;
-	Written operating procedures;
-	Mechanical integrity procedures for process equipment inspections and quality control;
-	Management of change and pre-startup safety review procedures;
-	Periodic, detailed Process Hazard Analysis by a team of qualified personnel with subject matter expertise;
-	Periodic audits of the PSM and RMP;
-	Employee participation;
-	Employee training and continuing education;
-	Incident investigation procedures;
-	Hot work permitting verifying the implementation of fire prevention and protection requirements prior to the beginning of hot work operations;
-	Coordination with local emergency and fire responders;
-	Stringent design standards of equipment which incorporate substantial safety factors and include state of the art monitoring and control instrumentation; and
-	Formal policies for contractor management
